    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Long, flexible, iridescent green tail plumes of the resplendant quetzal (Pharomachrus mocinno). These feathers held extremely high value in Nahua societies and were used in luxurious costumes, including back devices and headdresses.</Note_Text>
